displayName: Royal Capital Near Lake -Before the Castle Walls-

parameters:
After escaping the mining shaft and a long journey, Reisha
and Akane finally arrived at the royal capital, Near Lake.

What greeted them upon their return was the sight of
soldiers and citizens hurriedly running around the city,
busy with preparations for a military campaign.

The atmosphere was peculiar, as if everyone was being rushed
to deploy, which was enough to give the girls a premonition
that they were entering an exceptional situation.
What do you mean we can't pass through...?!

Gatekeeper: The royal capital is currently under strict
surveillance due to preparations for deployment.

Gatekeeper: No one is allowed to pass through as per the
regulations issued. I'm sorry, but no matter what you say,
we cannot let you into the royal capital right now.

I'm not insisting that you let us through by force. I admire
your dedication to your duty, even though you've been
summoned from various places as mercenaries.

Just send a messenger to the castle saying "Knight Reisha
has returned." That's all I ask. At least let me meet
someone from the castle who knows me. That should clear up
our situation.

Gatekeeper: If that's the case, then all the more reason we
cannot let you pass.
What did you say!?

Gatekeeper: "Be especially wary of those who claim to be
knights and show signs of communicating with the castle," we
have been strictly warned by the chancellor.
The chancellor... What does this mean...?

Gatekeeper: As we are in the midst of deployment
preparations, a variety of supplies and people are coming
and going in the royal capital. It's a prime opportunity for
unsavory thieves to sneak in. It's likely to avoid any
unnecessary trouble.

Gatekeeper: I understand it's an inconvenience, but I must
ask you to leave for today.
Damn it...! What in the world is going on!!

You can't let us through, that's absurd! The plan for the
monster subjugation in the west wasn't supposed to happen
until later. Why such elaborate preparations...?!
00_st_akane02_serious

Akane: Maybe it's just me thinking out loud here, but
weren't you supposed to be a knight as trusted as you claim?

I prided myself on fighting valiantly with my sword for my
lord... But having returned without fulfilling my given
mission, perhaps I'm not as esteemed as I thought...
00_st_akane02_nomal
Akane: Hey hey, I was just kidding! Cheer up!!
Merchant: Did you guys also get turned away at the gate?
You too means you weren't allowed through either?
Merchant: Yeah, exactly! Seriously!

Merchant: I came all this way with my goods because I heard
the royal capital was preparing for war with a neighboring
country. But they're just sticking to their guns about not
letting anyone through.

Merchant: Seriously, what a stingy move when there's a
chance to make a profit!
You, what did you just say...!

Merchant: Whoa! My apologies! I shouldn't have called your
country stingy...!
No, not that! The part before!!

Merchant: Eh? Eh? Are you talking about the royal capital
preparing for war with a neighboring country...??
Is that really true!?

Merchant: Ah, yeah... It's a rumor among us merchants, so we
tend to hear things sooner than others. It's reached even my
distant region, so I'd say it's almost certainly true.

Merchant: It's reached even my distant region, so I'd say
it's almost certainly true.

I apologize for raising my voice. Thank you for the
information.
Merchant: Oh, sure...
What does this mean. "Invading the neighboring country"?!

Such a plan should be impossible. The expedition was
supposed to be for the eradication of monster nests... What
is happening...?!

What is my lord thinking? What is happening to this
country?!

Ah! If only I could get some information now, but I'm not
even allowed to enter the royal capital!!
00_st_akane02_nomal
Akane: I don't really get what's going on, but...
Akane: So, you want information?

What has happened to the royal capital while I was away?
Right now, I want to know even a little about the situation.
00_st_akane02_nomal
Akane: Hmm.

Akane: Honestly, I was planning to receive a reward from you
and say goodbye once we reached the royal capital, but maybe
I can be of some help to you after all.
Akane: After all, I do owe you for your help.
00_st_akane02_serious

Akane: Standing around here isn't going to solve anything,
right?
Akane: I'll guide you, so come with me.
